\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Coherence dynamics comparison for three qubit architectures. Red dotted: standard transmon with exponential decay $\langle \sigma _x\rangle \propto e^{-\gamma t}$, $\gamma = 0.23$. Blue dashed: TRCA topological mode with reduced decay rate $\gamma = 0.05$. Green solid: fractal-resonant lattice with localization-enhanced coherence, $\gamma = 0.01$. The $23\times $ coherence improvement (transmon to fractal) supports the projected fidelity enhancement. Simulation: NumPy analytical approximation of Lindblad master equation.}}{7}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:coherence}{{2}{7}{Coherence dynamics comparison for three qubit architectures. Red dotted: standard transmon with exponential decay $\langle \sigma _x\rangle \propto e^{-\gamma t}$, $\gamma = 0.23$. Blue dashed: TRCA topological mode with reduced decay rate $\gamma = 0.05$. Green solid: fractal-resonant lattice with localization-enhanced coherence, $\gamma = 0.01$. The $23\times $ coherence improvement (transmon to fractal) supports the projected fidelity enhancement. Simulation: NumPy analytical approximation of Lindblad master equation}{figure.2}{}}
